Nollywood actress and film-maker Mary Remmy Njoku has said that Nigeria is a safe haven for unqualified foreign-trained cosmetic surgeons. The actress reacting to the demise of Instagram influencer Crystabel who llegedly died from complications while having some work done in a body enhancement Lagos clinicexplained that the unqualified surgeons will killing their clients if people continued blaming the victims. Sharing a post on her Instagram page she wrote, “Nigeria is a safe haven for bad IJGB cos-surgeons. Small accent and you are in business. -Advertisement- “Thanks to gullible Nigerians who make sure they continue Killing people by BLAMING THE VICTIMs. SAD. To those very few doctors who come home save lives. Thank you.”